FBIS4-14098 "drnes082_s_94015" FBIS-NES-94-082 Daily Report 27 Apr 1994 Iran MKO Radio Reportedly Hails Assassination Attempt MKO Radio Reportedly Hails Assassination Attempt LD2704122994 Tehran IRNA in English 1125 GMT 27 Apr 94 LD2704122994 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Tehran, April 27, IRNA -- The terrorist Mujahideen Khalq Organization (MKO) has backed the aborted attempt on the life of the substitute Friday prayer leader of Mashhad Hojjat ol-Eslam Aba'i Khorasani, on April 22. In a radio broadcast from Iraq, the terrorist grouplet described the failed assassination attempt as a popular move without mentioning its links with the assassin. An armed assailant, identified by the Ministry of Information as 'Ali Huri, shot and wounded Hojjat ol-Eslam Khorasani on Friday. He was later arrested by worshippers and handed over to police. Huri has confessed to his link with the Iraq-based terrorist grouplet and the MKO has not denied the link.
